 wizards I'd invite would tell me they wanted to group with their friends, wouldn't join until I got a cleric to heal them, or were afk.<br>
<br>
Beat your leader over the head with the fact that Bard songs on the MT will make the biggest difference for you over being anywhere else.  At 65 you can do 80ish AC, 100ish DS, and lots of ATK.  This is with my so-so instrument mods.  My guild always swapped MTs every boss fight, and I never could convince them to take 15 seconds to lock the raid and swap me into the new MT group.<br>
<br>
The only other group you should be in is a 5 DPS group, unless there is an AE, in which case 1 healer and 4 DPS.  Wizard, Rogue, Ranger.  Hopefully all spellcasters so you can do AE mana, or all melee so they all get Warsong.<br>
<br>
Next I would make sure they understand why they need multiple Bards.  I posted a list showing what positions Bards took.  When they see that one whole Bard is busy doing AE mana, AE resists, and debuffing resists and that's about his whole contribution to the raid, then they can start seeing why they want another Bard in the MT group and maybe a few more to pull, shield rampage tank, or just DPS. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=olorin00>olorin00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 370<br> <font color=#330000>(9/11/04 8:09 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19773.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: If you could tell a raid leader one thing...</span><hr size=1> I have passed by the same thing, trying to explain where they should put bard but even if some thing have been learned, the only real solution I found is: I (or another bard) make the groups (or at least the bard's group, so MT and DPS).<br>
